H3.text: Whose last words were Et Tu Brute according to Shakespeare. Caesar

A4.text: Shakespeare has Caesar remark Et tu, Brute? ('And you, Brutus?') before he dies.

A5.text: At this, Caesar asks 'Et tu, Brute?' ('You too, Brutus? '), concluding with 'Then fall, Caesar!'
